race.comment: Very competitive but SATURDAY SESH (2) is airborne and will take catching. Has won three of four this campaign, the latest at Kalgoorlie over the same trip when gave nothing else a chance. Unbeaten at this journey and has the inside so looks the one to run down. SWANSEE (6) resumed in the shorter race and was midfield in a career-worst run. Two back just missed this trip in open class and will relish the extra ground here after the fresh-up miss. Should improve sharply. CLIMB ON TOP (1) is going well and returned to winning form at Belmont Park last time over this journey racing on speed. One of the leading hopes again. GOLD MAKER (3) has been runner-up three on end and deserves a win. Hit the line hard to just miss over a mile last time and back a furlong will give a start but charge home. HE'S ARCHIE (7) was safely held in the same race as GOLD MAKER last time. Doesn't win out of turn but best figures measure up and could be over the odds.
